2. If we now inquire, Why the wrath of God is poured upon sinners, the reasons are at hand.

The first is derived from the Divine justice. For al· though God is not pleased with the sins of nien, yet he is pleased with his own righteousness, according to which, punishment is due to sinners. Therefore, it is not evil in God to punish the wicked, because it proceeds from the love of righteousness3 but the evil is in man, to deserve punishment3 because it proceeds from the love of wicked- ness.

The second is derived from human advantage. For this is the particular end of punishments‚ that they may effect the amendment of sinners.
